# Iteration 7 — Timings Feature Verification

## Criteria Verification

✓ `apps/board/src/db/schema.ts` defines three new nullable text columns: `inProgressAt`, `inReviewAt`, `shippedAt`. — Confirmed at lines 20-22: `inProgressAt: text('in_progress_at')`, `inReviewAt: text('in_review_at')`, `shippedAt: text('shipped_at')` — all nullable (no `.notNull()`).

✓ `apps/board/src/db/migrations.ts` includes all three columns in the `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` statement, plus `ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN` guards for existing databases. — Confirmed: `in_progress_at TEXT`, `in_review_at TEXT`, `shipped_at TEXT` present in CREATE TABLE (lines 17-19) and in the ALTER TABLE loop (lines 43-48).

✓ `moveCard()` in `apps/board/src/db/cards.ts` sets `inProgressAt` when transitioning to `in-progress`, `inReviewAt` when transitioning to `in-review`, and `shippedAt` when transitioning to `shipped`. — Confirmed at lines 89-91.

✓ `moveCard()` does NOT overwrite an already-set timestamp on re-entry (e.g., re-entering `in-progress` from `in-review` does not wipe `inProgressAt`). — Confirmed: each assignment guarded by `!existing?.inProgressAt` / `!existing?.inReviewAt` / `!existing?.shippedAt`.

✓ The `Card` type in `apps/board/src/components/BoardClient.tsx` includes `inProgressAt`, `inReviewAt`, and `shippedAt` as optional string fields. — Confirmed at lines 22-24.

✓ `CardPanel.tsx` displays each timestamp when non-null (e.g., "In Progress at: …") and shows computed durations for completed stage transitions. — Confirmed in `buildMarkdown()` lines 211-233: backlog wait, in-progress duration, in-review duration, total duration all computed and rendered.

✓ `board show <id>` CLI output includes timing fields (timestamps and computed durations) when present. — Confirmed in `bin/board` cmdShow: lines for `inProgressAt`, `inReviewAt`, `shippedAt` with duration calculations, guarded by field presence.

✓ Running `bun test` passes with no new failures. — Confirmed: 74 pass, 0 fail.

✓ Existing cards with NULL timing columns render without errors in the UI and CLI. — Confirmed: all display logic gated by `if (card.inProgressAt)` etc. in both CardPanel and CLI; absent fields produce no output, no errors.
